The paper deals with the combinatorial and geometric properties of graphs in the plane, specifically thrackles. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial arguments and graph theory, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Graph Theory) as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the edge-vertex ratio of thrackles, which is a measure of their density, indicating that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible sub-categories.
